codex
I found a concrete flaw in the current verifier itself: it “refutes” the finding with a zero-amount `transferFrom(self,self,0)` probe, but zero-amount probes are not discriminating because standard ERC20 implementations also let an allowance check pass for `amount == 0`. I’m replacing that with a funded nonzero probe, keeping the repay path order intact, and switching funding to a v2-first / Balancer-fallback flow so the verifier can honestly distinguish WETH-style self-transfer semantics from the reported failure mode.
apply patch
